22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Review%3A%20The%20Broken%20News%20S2%20Does%20Not%20Fluff%20Its%20Lines%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERuminations%20on%20the%20ethics%20of%20news%20journalism%20follow%20a%20freewheeling%20yet%20tortuous%20path%20in%20Season%202%20of%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%3C%2Fi%3E%20as%20professional%20principles%20and%20personal%20prejudices%20collide%20in%20a%20deleterious%20and%20bruising%20battle%20for%20supremacy%20between%20two%20television%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eight-episode%20Zee5%20series%2C%20fronted%20by%20Sonali%20Bendre%2C%20Jaideep%20Ahlawat%20and%20Shriya%20Pilgaonkar%2C%20explores%20the%20labyrinths%20of%20an%20all-out%20war%20of%20agendas%20and%20belief%20systems%20and%20presents%20an%20engaging%20tale%20of%20a%20clutch%20of%20journalists%20who%20labour%20to%20sift%20fact%20from%20falsehood%2C%20sach%20(truth)%20from%20sansani%20(sensationalism)%2C%20and%20public%20interest%20from%20propaganda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20in%20the%20capital%20city%20of%20a%20large%20state%20where%20an%20opposition%20leader%20(Sandesh%20Kulkarni)%20mounts%20a%20political%20campaign%20against%20the%20chief%20minister%20(Srikant%20Yadav)%2C%20the%20show%2C%20adapted%20from%20a%20BBC%20One%20series%2C%20centres%20on%20two%20leading%20national%20news%20channels%20who%20take%20sides%20and%20continually%20snipe%20at%20each%20other%2C%20reflecting%20the%20bitterness%20of%20the%20clash%20of%20ideologies%20unfolding%20in%20the%20larger%20arena%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20executed%20with%20consistent%20competence%20and%20awareness%20of%20the%20times%2C%20is%20a%20tale%20of%20political%20crimes%2C%20a%20newsroom%20drama%20and%20a%20revenge%20saga%20that%20builds%20its%20plot%20around%20events%20that%20have%20been%20in%20the%20news%20in%20the%20real%20world%20of%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20strewn%20with%20references%20to%20data%20theft%2C%20troll%20armies%2C%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20a%20mass%20suicide%2C%20an%20app-based%20moneylending%20racket%2C%20the%20death%20of%20a%20social%20media%20influencer%2C%20a%20midday%20meal%20scam%2C%20the%20mysterious%20demise%20of%20a%20geologist%2C%20an%20attempted%20cover-up%20of%20a%20water%20contamination%20case%20and%2C%20inevitably%2C%20the%20big%20industry%20seeking%20to%20control%20the%20flow%20of%20news%20and%20the%20exercise%20of%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20way%20too%20much%20to%20handle%20in%20a%20single%20season%20of%20a%20series%3F%20It%20perhaps%20is.%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20at%20times%20undermined%20a%20touch%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20has%20to%20resort%20to%20hurried%20board%20strokes.%20That%20apart%2C%20a%20degree%20of%20confusion%20creeps%20in%20when%20it%20adopts%20simplistic%20methods%20to%20draw%20of%20battle%20lines%20between%20opposing%20worldviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20does%20not%20major%20damage%20to%20the%20overall%20outcome%20it%20is%20because%20the%20script%20ensures%20that%20there%20is%20just%20enough%20happening%20in%20the%20narrative%20at%20a%20pace%20that%20rules%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20momentary%20snags%20sticking%20out%20and%20slowing%20down%20the%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20follow-up%20to%20the%20Vinay%20Waikul-directed%202022%20newsroom%20drama%20series%2C%20writer%20Sambit%20Mishra%20falls%20back%20on%20newsy%20titbits%20to%20rustle%20up%20an%20intriguing%20story%20that%20touches%20upon%20pertinent%20themes%20with%20the%20seriousness%20that%20they%20merit.%20Not%20that%20all%20of%20it%20hits%20home%20with%20equal%20force%2C%20but%20parts%20of%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20Season%202%3C%2Fi%3E%20do%20strike%20a%20chord%20and%20provoke%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAided%20by%20strong%20and%20steady%20performances%20from%20the%20lead%20actors%20and%20the%20supporting%20cast%20(Sanjeeta%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Faisal%20Rashid%2C%20Taaruk%20Raina%2C%20Indraneil%20Sengupta%20and%20two%20key%20news%20additions%2C%20Geetika%20Vidya%20Ohlyan%20and%20Akshay%20Oberoi)%2C%20the%20show%20wends%20its%20way%20through%20a%20series%20of%20events%20that%20elicit%20divergent%20responses%20from%20two%20news%20channels%20run%20by%20two%20individuals%20whose%20approaches%20to%20journalism%20are%20diametrically%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJostling%20for%20power%2C%20pelf%20and%20position%2C%20the%20journos%20vent%20their%20feelings%20and%20beliefs%20in%20edit%20meetings%20and%20on%20prime%20time%20shows.%20Season%201%20had%20ended%20with%20Radha%20Bhargava%20(Pilgaonkar)%20of%20Awaaz%20Bharati%2C%20a%20channel%20headed%20by%20Amina%20Qureshi%20(Bendre)%2C%20being%20jailed%20after%20Dipankar%20Sanyal%20(Ahlawat)%2C%20editor-in%20chief%20of%20Josh%2024%2F7%20network%2C%20brands%20her%20an%20%26quot%3Banti-national%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHalfway%20through%20the%20opening%20episode%20of%20Season%202%2C%20Radha%20gets%20bail.%20She%20plunges%20right%20back%20into%20her%20ongoing%20tussle%20with%20Dipankar%2C%20who%2C%20on%20his%20part%2C%20does%20not%20budge%20an%20inch%20from%20his%20pursuit%20of%20eyeballs.%20Terms%20like%20'virtue%20signalling'%20and%20'confirmation%20bias'%20are%20heard%20as%20the%20journalists%20debate%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadha%2C%20young%2C%20uncompromising%20and%20wedded%20to%20a%20cause%2C%20seeks%20to%20harness%20of%20power%20of%20truth%20as%20a%20means%20to%20settling%20scores%20her%20bete%20noire%2C%20the%20man%20responsible%20for%20her%20stint%20in%20prison%20where%20she%20has%20slighted%20and%20tortured%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%20of%20trying%20to%20right%20the%20wrongs%20done%20to%20her%2C%20Radha%20appears%20to%20blur%20the%20line%20that%20separates%20the%20journalist%20and%20the%20activist%20in%20her.%20It%20is%20a%20tightrope%20walk.%20There%20is%20a%20price%20to%20pay%20as%20Radha%20opens%20up%20several%20fronts%20and%20plunges%20headlong%20into%20the%20complexities%20of%20a%20multiplicity%20of%20stories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20own%20newsroom%2C%20Radha%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20her%20mentor%20and%20friend%2C%20Amina%2C%20an%20old%20school%20journalist%20who%20swears%20by%20objectivity.%20Those%20who%20speak%20the%20truth%2C%20Amina%20says%2C%20are%20often%20isolated.%20She%20accuses%20Radha%20of%20allowing%20her%20anger%20to%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F2M29LWMXrdA%3Fsi%3DKkJ6KF1_CF8kvOuT%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20their%20newsroom%20stands%20the%20towering%20and%20pro-establishment%20Dipankar%2C%20who%20brings%20a%20third%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20business%20of%20news.%20TRPs%20mean%20the%20world%20to%20him.%20A%20self-styled%20voice%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20he%20signs%20off%20his%20news%20shows%20with%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3EYeh%20sawaal%20hai%20desh%20ka%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehana%20Ahmed%20(Ohlyan)%2C%20who%20moves%20from%20reporting%20on%20Bollywood%20stars%20to%20chasing%20hardcore%20news%20and%20anchoring%20shows%2C%20represents%20another%20face%20of%20journalism.%20From%20an%20underprivileged%20background%2C%20work%20is%20a%20daily%20grind%20and%20a%20necessity.%20%26quot%3B%3Ci%3EDeshbhakt%20marne%20tak%3C%2Fi%3E%26quot%3B%20are%20the%20words%20that%20she%20rounds%20off%20her%20shows%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20single%20mother%20struggling%20to%20get%20ahead%20in%20life%20and%20ensure%20that%20her%20son%20secures%20admission%20in%20a%20quality%20school%2C%20Rehana%20frequently%20displeases%20her%20boss%20at%20Josh%2024%2F7%20with%20her%20impulsive%20ways.%20She%20is%20taken%20to%20task%20but%20she%20carries%20on%20regardless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20there%20is%20Ranjit%20%26quot%3BRonnie%26quot%3B%20Sabharwal%20(Oberoi)%2C%20who%20takes%20over%20as%20the%20business%20head%20of%20Awaaz%20Bharati%20as%20a%20representative%20of%20a%20tech%20giant%20that%20is%20readying%20itself%20to%20roll%20out%20thousands%20of%20EVs%20in%20India.%20News%20as%20an%20assembly%20line%20commodity%20meant%20to%20be%20bought%20and%20consumed%20like%20any%20other%20product%20in%20the%20market%20-%20that%20supposition%20represents%20one%20of%20the%20principal%20strands%20of%20the%20saga.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20was%20the%20case%20in%20Season%201%2C%20the%20newsroom%20showdowns%20and%20shenanigans%20in%20S2%20are%20held%20together%20by%20the%20performances.%20While%20Sonali%20Bendre%20and%20Jaideep%20Ahlawat%20deliver%20pitch-perfect%20interpretations%20of%20two%20different%20kinds%20of%20reporters%2C%20the%20real%20star%20of%20Season%202%20is%20Shriya%20Pilgaonkar.%20She%20traverses%20an%20entire%20gamut%20of%20mercurial%20emotions%20with%20impressive%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeetika%20Vidya%20Ohlyan%2C%20playing%20a%20conflicted%20and%20often%20embattled%20reporter%2C%20sways%20between%20the%20highs%20and%20lows%20of%20the%20character's%20arc%20without%20missing%20a%20beat.%20Akshay%20Oberoi%20as%20the%20suave%20corporate%20honcho%20running%20a%20news%20operation%20captures%2C%20with%20a%20keen%20sense%20of%20the%20issues%20at%20play%2C%20the%20contradictions%20and%20challenges%20that%20the%20man%20faces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20stray%20blips%20notwithstanding%2C%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Broken%20News%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%20does%20not%20fluff%20its%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714714320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fslvtd5d8_-broken-news_625x300_03_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fthe-broken-news-s2-review-does-not-fluff-its-lines-a-few-stray-blips-notwithstanding-2-5-stars-5