ren%20Colananni%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-advice-rental-property-income-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommon%20passive%20income%20streams%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20millionaires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColananni%20says%20that%20having%20homes%20that%20are%20rented%20out%20year-round%2C%20or%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20year%2C%20can%20provide%20not%20only%20a%20stream%20of%20steady%20income%20but%20can%20also%20have%20tax%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColananni%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20get%20a%20tax%20deduction%20on%20the%20rental%20income%20by%20depreciating%20the%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20deducting%20the%20cost%20of%20buying%20or%20improving%20a%20rental%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20use%20any%20expenses%20(including%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20utilities%2C%20normal%20repairs%2C%20etc.)%20to%20help%20offset%20your%20rental-property%20income%20by%20deducting%20this%20from%20your%20own%20personal%20tax%20obligations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20means%20that%20some%20portion%20of%20the%20income%20is%20coming%20to%20you%20tax-free%20while%20you%20continue%20to%20build%20equity%20in%20the%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Social%20Security%2C%20collected%20strategically%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20passive%20income%20stream%20that%20most%20American%20workers%20get%20when%20they%20retire%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20one%20that%20millionaires%20also%20bank%20on%2C%20according%20to%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fscott-sturgeon-jd-mba-cfp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScott%20Sturgeon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20says%20that%20while%20Social%20Security%20is%20a%20common%20income%20stream%2C%20there's%20an%20ideal%20timeline%20for%20starting%20those%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSocial%20Security%20planning%20can%20get%20surprisingly%20complicated%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sturgeon.%20%26quot%3BFor%20my%20clients%2C%20I%20run%20various%20analyses%20to%20determine%20when%20the%20optimal%20time%20to%20start%20those%20payments%20might%20be%20based%20on%20their%20specific%20financial%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20can%20start%20receiving%20your%20Social%20Security%20retirement%20benefits%20at%2062%2C%20if%20you%20wait%20to%20take%20payments%20until%20you%20reach%20age%2070%2C%20the%20amount%20you%20receive%20will%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20won't%20help%20me%20if%20I%20retire%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eearly%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20I%20can%20count%20on%20it%20later%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Investing%20in%20a%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20once%20his%20millionaire%20clients%20stop%20working%20full-time%20and%20retire%2C%20financial%20advisor%20Brian%20See%20has%20noticed%20that%20they're%20still%20involved%20in%20businesses%20as%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESee%20says%20clients%20invest%20in%20businesses%20in%20many%20different%20ways%2C%20from%20investing%20in%20start-ups%20to%20providing%20a%20company%20with%20a%20capital%20infusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvesting%20in%20these%20businesses%20gives%20you%20ownership%20in%20a%20company%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20possibly%20access%20royalties%2C%20profit%20sharing%2C%20or%20the%20opportunity%20to%20sell%20the%20businesses%20for%20capital%20gains%20at%20a%20potential%20future%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20See.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpassive-income-strea